<br>
Here's my opinion.  It seems like the arguments against gay marriage is becoming more obsolete, since more people are now seeing that homosexuality is a natural thing.  I saw one old guy in Newsweek holding a protest sign that said &quot;Homosexuality: Hellfire Sin&quot; and some representative saying &quot;There can only be one true union of two human beings, and that is the union of a man and a woman.&quot;  Both made me laugh.  <br>
<br>
Homophobia is still so prevalent.  It all seems pretty absurd to me, considering I grew up in Cali and was educated to accept gay people.  My mom is homophobic too but she won't discuss why.  I guess homophobic people just have a kind of revulsion that is built into their brains.<br>
<br>
The only thing I see going against gay couples, is that they can't have kids (taking away one of the reasons for marriage benefits), although a lot of them do adopt kids.  And also, I think pictures of two guys kissing each other is gross. =D <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/ping000/Rasc-sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
