<br>
The main oposition a lot of gays meet stems from the fact that many homosexuals are very obvious and flagrant about it.  Let homosexuals do what they want, as I said, but just because they can doesn't mean they should show affection everywhere they go.  A lot of people are disgusted by a heterosexual couple with public displays of affection, not because it's wrong but because it's just not the place or time.  I'm just as offened by a homosexual couple doing more than holding hands, hugging and kissing as I am with a heterosexual couple doing it.<br>
<br>
The phrase &quot;Get a room&quot; sums it up.<br>
<br>
While homosexuality is becoming socially acceptable, don't get me started on how certain things, like discrimination in the work place, will never ever work when applied to homosexuality.<br>
<br>
I'm all for homosexual rights, but keep it private.  Just because you can do something doesn't mean you should.  Love is love, but a little self control goes a long way.<br>
<br>
Aerdor Dewcatcher<br>
53rd druid<br>
