<br>
There are lots of straight couples out there who never have kids, and lots of them have vasectomies so they never can have kids.  Are you against them?<br>
<br>
What about the gay couples who don't give birth to kids, but raise them?  Across the street from me is a lesbian couple who's raising a couple of kids and sending them to school.  Isn't that helping propagate our species? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=baelor>Baelor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#330000>(7/9/03 10:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=832.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Gay Marriages</span><hr size=1> Extending marriage rights to homosexual couples can and often does have very little to do with homophobia.<br>
<br>
I don't think that society should do anything to promote what really is an aberration of nature.  Before you people start jumping on me for being a homophobe, that is not the case.  I am not passing judgement.  Just because something isn't natural, that doesn't necessarily make it wrong or bad...I simply think that homosexuality isn't in the best interest of any species.<br>
<br>
Do what you want (or who you want) in your private life...I don't care.  Take any job you want and I believe you shouldn't be descriminated against.  If you are cool and become my friend, but are gay, I don't really care (as long as it isn't pushed under my nose inappropriately).  But sanctioning marriage?  Why?<br>
<br>
