<br>
Before they get brought up, as they probably will, let's dispell some things:<br>
<br>
Although the sole function of a species is to survive through future generations, I think it's safe to admit that Humanity has moved passed that.  Humans and dolphins are the only known species to derive pleasure from sexual intercourse.  Therefore, deviances will happen for the pursuit of pleasure.<br>
<br>
Homosexuality is not genetic.  If it was, there wouldn't be any gay people since they can't pass down their genes to future generations.  No saying that homosexuals are born that way and they can't help it.<br>
<br>
Until the past 150 years, marriage had always been an economic or political thing.  This whole &quot;love&quot; thing that scares the uptight polititians and conservatives is just now starting to get worked into law.  A lot of it is still viewed as economic, and is why Vermont, and any state considering homosexual union, has yet to allow homosexuals the benefits of marriage.<br>
<br>
You can't stop homosexual discrimination in the work place short of having the government issue a sexual preferences license.  Why?  Some heterosexuals look gay, and some homosexuals look straight.  And if homosexual anti-discrimination is sanctioned (RE: Affirmative Action for gays), there's nothing stopping a straight person from claiming homosexuality and thus benefitting from something that doesn't apply to them.  And I really doubt anyone actually wants to have to carry around a sexual preferences license...<br>
<br>
