<br>
I have no problem with gay marriages. It's really none of my business what Jim and Joe do behind closed doors, and if they want to do it with the legality of a marriage contract, more power to them.<br>
<br>
I think some of the &quot;protest&quot; against gay marriages comes not just from a religious standpoint but a financial one.  Insurance companies do NOT want to cover same-sex spouses.  Employers don't want to deal with loss-of-wage issues when a same sex spouse wants to take off under the family leave act.  <br>
<br>
It's just easier to claim a religious objection than it is to claim a selfish objection.   <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:green;font-family:georgia;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Meridian Ascendant</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
